sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as Apiserver<br/>Configurable Port<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant FS as File Store<br/>S3 (443/TCP) / FS
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>Worker Pool
    participant IGW as Inference Gateway<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,IGW: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission & Execution

        Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart upload)<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
        API->>FS: Store file content<br/>HTTPS (S3) / Local (FS)
        API->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TCP, TLS (optional)
        API-->>Client: 200 OK {file_id}

        Client->>API: POST /v1/batches {input_file_id}<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
        API->>PG: Create batch record<br/>TCP, TLS (optional)
        API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue (sorted set)<br/>TCP, TLS (optional)
        API-->>Client: 200 OK {batch_id, status: validating}

        Proc->>Redis: Dequeue job (BLMPop)<br/>TCP, TLS (optional)
        Redis-->>Proc: Job payload with priority
        Proc->>FS: Download input JSONL<br/>HTTPS (S3) / Local
        FS-->>Proc: Input file content
        Proc->>PG: Update status → in_progress

        loop For each request in JSONL (concurrent)
            Proc->>IGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization: Bearer {api-key}<br/>TLS 1.2+ (configurable)
            IGW-->>Proc: Completion response
            Proc->>Redis: Update progress counter
        end

        Proc->>FS: Upload output JSONL<br/>HTTPS (S3) / Local
        Proc->>PG: Update status → completed<br/>Set output_file_id
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over Client,IGW: Flow 2: Batch Cancellation

        Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username
        API->>Redis: Publish cancel event (LPUSH)<br/>TCP
        Redis-->>Proc: Cancel notification (BLMPop)
        Proc->>FS: Upload partial output JSONL
        Proc->>PG: Update status → cancelled
        API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: cancelling}
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,IGW: Flow 3: Garbage Collection

        Note over Proc: batch-gateway-gc (periodic)
        Proc->>PG: Query expired batches/files<br/>WHERE expires_at < NOW()
        PG-->>Proc: Expired record list
        Proc->>FS: Delete expired file content
        Proc->>PG: Delete expired metadata records
    end
